==English==

===Etymology===
Shortened form of "How do you do?"

===Interjection===
'''howdy'''

# (''US, generally rural'') An informal greeting.
#: ''Howdy folks, and welcome to our ninth annual chili cookoff!''
===Noun and Pronoun===
'''howdy'''
# (''British archaic'') A greeting. Short for how-d'ye-do.
===Noun===
'''howdy''' or '''howdie'''
# (''Scottish'') A wife, a midwife.

